    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1951-10-03T16:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1951-10-03T16:00:00-05:00" n="653"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d653">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">394.31/10–351: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Canada</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Woodward</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">priority</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Ottawa</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1951-10-03T16:00:00-05:00"
                            >October 3, 1951—4 p. m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received October 9—2:23 p. m.<note n="1" xml:id="d653fn1">Typewritten
                            notation at the bottom of the page reads: “Message delayed in
                            transmission. Passed to Geneva, Paris, 10–9–51, 2:35 p.
                        m.”</note>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>57. From Willoughby. <gloss target="#t_Embtel1">Embtel</gloss> 53, Sept 28.
                    Canadians agree generally with substance <gloss target="#t_Deptel1"
                        >Deptel</gloss> Gatt 33 Sept 22. US position, however, apparently based on
                    assumption Belg restrictions not yet in effect. Canadians now certain licenses
                    being refused imports from Canada.</p>
                <p>Canadian Govt, therefore, instructing its del <gloss target="#t_GATT1"
                        >GATT</gloss> today to take immediate steps to seek removal existing
                    restrictions. First Canadian approach will be informal through Isbister<note
                        n="2" xml:id="d653fn2">C. M. Isbister of the Canadian Department of Trade
                        and Commerce, member of the Canadian Delegation at Geneva.</note> to head
                    Belg del Geneva. If ineffective, formal complaint to <gloss target="#t_CP1"
                        >CP</gloss>s planned.</p>
                <p>Belg case will set important precedent. While full info re activities <gloss
                        target="#t_EPU1">EPU</gloss> and <gloss target="#t_OEEC1">OEEC</gloss> not
                    available here, vigorous action objecting restrictions appears imperative.
                    Sterling area countries cld reasonably contend their monetary arrangements
                    analogous to <gloss target="#t_EPU1">EPU</gloss>. If US acquiesces
                    discriminatory import restrictions under good current condition Belg reserves
                    and balance payments, we will have undermined basis for insisting elimination
                    discriminatory restrictions by sterling area countries as the balance payments
                    improve.</p>
                <p>From standpoint Canada as well as other countries Belg precedent dangerous.
                    Canada has over-all current account deficit resulting chiefly from heavy trade
                    deficit with US. Serious balance payments difficulties <pb facs="1503" n="1487"
                        xml:id="pg_1487"/> not impending but situation cld change rapidly. A large
                    reduction in capital imports which now offset current account deficit wld immed
                    confront Canada with problem of reducing trade deficit and strong pressure for
                    discriminatory restrictions against US trade wld develop.</p>
                <p>Dept pass Geneva, Paris. Sent Dept priority 57, rptd priority Geneva (for <gloss
                        target="#t_USDel1">USDel</gloss>
                    <gloss target="#t_GATT1">GATT</gloss>) unn, Paris (for <gloss target="#t_OSR1"
                        >OSR</gloss>) unn. [Willoughby.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Woodward</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
